<P>Thus se you neyghboures, that Christ the gyfte of God, which bryn+geth saluacion to all men, hathe ap|pered yea &amp; that in the flesh, whiche he receaued of the moost blyssed and pure virgine Mary He appered, say one S. Iohn~,<NOTE PLACE="marg">i. Ioan. iii.</NOTE> that he myghte <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> awaye our synnes, &amp; yet was there <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> in hym. Agayne, for thys
